Package server.Model

Class Shelf

java.lang.Object
Observer.ShelfObservable
server.Model.Shelf
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, SimpleShelf
public class Shelf extends ShelfObservable implements Serializable, SimpleShelf
This Class represents the Shelf of a single Player as described in the game rules. The Shelf consists in a bi-dimensional array of PlayableItemTiles which generates a matrix with 6 rows and 5 columns. Have a look at MyShelfie RuleBook for further information

    • setPointsAdj

      public void setPointsAdj(int pointsAdj)
      Sets the total amount of adjacency points scored by a Player. Adjacency points are awarded to a Player when groups of adjacent PlayableItemTiles with the same Colour of determined size are present in the Shelf.
      Parameters:
      pointsAdj - the amount of adjacency points to award to a Player

    • countMaxVoidTilesShelfColumns

      public int countMaxVoidTilesShelfColumns()
      Method that counts, for every column of the structure of a Shelf, the number of cells which contain a PlayableItemTile with Colour VOID and idCode that is equal to -1. Then the method computes the maximum between the results, which represents the maximum number of tiles that could be picked in the livingRoom in a single turn.
      Returns:
      the maximum between the values of available cells in each column of the Shelf's structure

    • isFull

      public boolean isFull()
      Returns:
      false if there is at least one cell in the Shelf which does not contain a PlayableItemTile with Colour different from VOID and idCode different from -1, true otherwise

    • getColumnChosen

      public int getColumnChosen()
      Returns:
